how often I get crema de coco in my coffee. Sometimes I am able to drink my coffee black but usually my mouth puckers and then half the drink goes down the sink.

I think one time I counted 44 sneakily emptied drinks just for sake of not shedding an offended eyebrow at the counter. I mean really, whether it is a glass of water or wine or tea that gets spiked with cream, this being my big issue is a serious exaggeration.

When it comes to where I live on Caye Caulker, I could make a case for many cost of living advantages being available to an expat; for example: no scary urban driving, but on the other hand there are irresponsible locals on bikes, pedestrians, dogs and more rather than mere cars. It keeps things interesting and a bit more lively than a typical day in Boise, Idaho. But if you are an architecture lover, for example, you may not find the living quarters quite so pleasing. For the grandiose homes on the island they come with pretty steep prices even when you aren’t gaining a drawback perspective.

Then there is the tropical setting, and it’s not that I’m a fan of insects, right now I have horned beetles as dinner guests flitting around about the size of my pinky nail on the ceiling.
